               <p>SAMUEL BARBER. I <rs id="t18261026-124-viclabel683" type="occupation">keep the <placeName id="t18261026-124-crimeloc684">Crooked Billet public-house, Portsmouth-street, Lincoln's Inn-fields</placeName>
                     <interp inst="t18261026-124-crimeloc684" type="placeName" value="Crooked Billet public-house, Portsmouth-street, Lincoln's Inn-fields"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18261026-124-crimeloc684" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                     <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18261026-124-off681 t18261026-124-crimeloc684"></join>
                  </rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18261026-124-victim817 t18261026-124-viclabel683"></join>. On the 7th of October the prisoner was at my house from one to four o'clock, when he went up the bed-room stairs; my daughter went up, and alarmed me - I ran, and saw the prisoner coming down stairs - he ran out; I followed, and found this property on him - the shirt and cap were in his hat; they were taken from the drawers.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182610260076"></xptr>
            
                  <persName id="t18261026-124-person818">
                  WILLIAM 
                  WHEATLEY
